enumDescriptions: TPU node state is not known/set.
TPU node is being repaired and may be unusable. Details can be found in the 'help_description' field.
TPU node has been preempted. Only applies to Preemptible TPU Nodes.
TPU node has been terminated due to maintenance or has reached the end of its life cycle (for preemptible nodes).
state.description: Output only. The current state for the TPU Node.

metadata.description: Custom metadata to apply to the TPU Node. Can set startup-script and shutdown-script

healthDescription.description: Output only. If this field is populated, it contains a description of why the TPU Node is unhealthy.

symptoms.description: Output only. The Symptoms that have occurred to the TPU Node.

name.description: Output only. Immutable. The name of the TPU.

labels.description: Resource labels to represent user-provided metadata.

dataDisks.description: The additional data disks for the Node.

networkEndpoints.description: Output only. The network endpoints where TPU workers can be accessed and sent work. It is recommended that runtime clients of the node reach out to the 0th entry in this map first.

cidrBlock.description: The CIDR block that the TPU node will use when selecting an IP address. This CIDR block must be a /29 block; the Compute Engine networks API forbids a smaller block, and using a larger block would be wasteful (a node can only consume one IP address). Errors will occur if the CIDR block has already been used for a currently existing TPU node, the CIDR block conflicts with any subnetworks in the user's provided network, or the provided network is peered with another network that is using that CIDR block.

enumDescriptions: Health status is unknown: not initialized or failed to retrieve.
The in-guest ML stack is unhealthy.
The node is under maintenance/priority boost caused rescheduling and will resume running once rescheduled.

enumDescriptions: TPU runtime is out of memory.
TPU runtime execution has timed out.
TPU runtime fails to construct a mesh that recognizes each TPU device's neighbors.
TPU HBM is out of memory.
Abusive behaviors have been identified on the current project.

subnetwork.description: The name of the subnetwork for the TPU node. It must be a preexisting Google Compute Engine subnetwork. If none is provided, "default" will be used.

canIpForward.description: Allows the TPU node to send and receive packets with non-matching destination or source IPs. This is required if you plan to use the TPU workers to forward routes.

enableExternalIps.description: Indicates that external IP addresses would be associated with the TPU workers. If set to false, the specified subnetwork or network should have Private Google Access enabled.
